 ----------ABOUT THE PROJECT----------
 This is a Streamlit Phone Number Country Detector,a Beginner’s Toolkit
Technology Used: Python + Streamlit
what It does :
It allows the user to input a phone number then get info on where the number is from( country),service providers in the detected country and Mobile money services.
---------TO DO SUCH A PROJECT (REQUIREMENTS)---------------

1. Operating System: Windows / Linux / MacOS
2. Tools / Editors: VS Code (recommended)
3.  Have python version 3.11+ is installed and added to PATH
-> to check your python version : 
* open your terminal 
* and type: python --version
* if you don't have a 3.11+  python version or you are having an error saying Python executable is not availabe in your path,you can:
a.  Download and install Python from the official website: https://www.python.org/downloads/
b.  During installation, ensure you check the box that says "Add Python to PATH"
c.  After installation, restart your terminal and try running      python --version 
to confirm Python is available.
4. Then, you can create your virtual environment with:
   python -m venv venv
5. Python Packages:
streamlit:pip install streamlit
phonenumbers:pip install phonenumbers pycountry emoji
6. Optional: Git (for version control and GitHub integration)
7. Write the code with the Logic and functionalities ( check the app.py file for details code and comments)
---------IF YOU WANT THIS PROJECT RUNNING ON YOUR LOCAL MACHINE-----
1. Installation & Setup Instructions
Step 1: Clone the Repository
git clone <https://github.com/lusamaki/StreamLit_Starter.git>
cd streamlit-beginner-toolkit (Or the folder in which you want it to be stored)
Step 2: Create Virtual Environment
python -m venv venv
Activate it:
•	Git Bash / Linux / MacOS: 
source venv/Scripts/activate  # Windows Git Bash
•	PowerShell (Windows): 
venv\Scripts\activate
Step 3: Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
(requirements.txt contains: streamlit and phonenumbers)
Step 4: Run the App
streamlit run app.py
•	Open your browser if it doesn’t open automatically. 
•	URL will look like: http://localhost:8501 
